<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1441,802,1114]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,802,826]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<collectingRegion box="[387,473,802,826]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Mexico</collectingRegion>
locality was previously reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, R. M." box="[923,1087,802,826]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref26743" refString="Young, R. M. 1988. A monograph of the genus Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum 11: vi + 115 p." type="book" year="1988">Young (1988)</bibRefCitation>
as from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1346,1436,802,826]" country="Mexico" name="Sonora" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Sonora</collectingRegion>
. Revised locality data cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="McCleve, S. &amp; B. Kohlmann" box="[566,951,833,858]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="17 - 28" refId="ref24481" refString="McCleve, S., and B. Kohlmann 2005. New species and new records of Copris (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae) from Mexico and the United States. Zootaxa 1096: 17 - 28." type="journal article" year="2005">McCleve and Kohlmann (2005)</bibRefCitation>
indicate this locality is actually within the southwestern border of the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[677,819,866,890]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1441,802,1114]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
This species was not listed from 
<collectingRegion box="[638,748,898,922]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Colorado</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, R. M." box="[791,948,898,922]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="279 - 318" refId="ref26655" refString="Young, R. M. 1967. Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Part I: the diffracta complex (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 93: 279 - 318." type="journal article" year="1967">Young (1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, R. M." box="[960,1023,898,922]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref26743" refString="Young, R. M. 1988. A monograph of the genus Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum 11: vi + 115 p." type="book" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Krell, F. - T." box="[1042,1189,898,922]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref23969" refString="Krell, F. - T. 2010. Catalog of Colorado Scarabs and Stag Beetles (Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea) based on literature records. Technical Report 2010 - 4. Denver Museum of Nature and Science; Denver, CO. 84 p." type="book" year="2010">Krell (2010)</bibRefCitation>
cites “Mesa County, 
<collectingRegion box="[192,305,930,954]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Colorado</collectingRegion>
.” Records of its occurrence in 
<collectingRegion box="[670,794,930,954]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">California</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Young, R. M." box="[810,959,930,954]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="279 - 318" refId="ref26655" refString="Young, R. M. 1967. Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Part I: the diffracta complex (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 93: 279 - 318." type="journal article" year="1967">Young 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Young, R. M." box="[971,1033,930,954]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" refId="ref26743" refString="Young, R. M. 1988. A monograph of the genus Polyphylla Harris in America, north of Mexico. Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum 11: vi + 115 p." type="book" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, A. V." box="[1045,1190,930,954]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref23263" refString="Evans, A. V. 1992. Checklist of the Scarabaeoidea of California. Scarabs Newsletter 7: 1 - 10. (Available at ~ http: // coleopsoc. org. Last accessed January 2016)." type="journal article" year="1992">Evans 1992</bibRefCitation>
) certainly represent misidentified or mislabeled specimens. For example, examination of a male specimen in the SBMNH determined as this species and labeled “Calif: San Bernardino Co., San Bernardino NF, nr. Deer Crk. 
<geoCoordinate box="[192,290,1026,1050]" degrees="34.1741" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" precision="5" value="34.1741">34.1741</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[290,412,1026,1050]" degrees="116.9844" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" precision="5" value="-116.9844">-116.9844</geoCoordinate>
, 
<date box="[424,577,1025,1050]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" value="2005-07-02">July 2, 2005</date>
, specimen #CBP0031851, M. Caterino collector” shows that, in fact, it represents 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1856" box="[330,445,1058,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinita">
<emphasis box="[330,445,1058,1081]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. crinita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with fragmented elytral vittae (see comments regarding this character under 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. rugosipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below).
</paragraph>
